---
# =============================================================================
#  PUBLICATIONS BIBLIOGRAPHY
# =============================================================================
#  This file is rendered into /publications/ by the jekyll-scholar plugin.
#  Entries are grouped by year (descending) in _config.yml.
#
#  HOW TO ADD A NEW PAPER  (step by step)
#  --------------------------------------
#    1. Get the BibTeX. Most journals have a "Cite / Export" button; or paste
#       the DOI into https://www.doi2bib.org/ to generate it.
#    2. Give it a unique citekey: lastnameYEARkeyword
#       (e.g. golmohammadi2026sensors). This is what you cite on project pages.
#    3. (Optional) Thumbnail: drop a small JPG (~600x400, the graphical
#       abstract or first page works well) into
#         assets/img/publication_preview/publications/
#       and point to it with:  preview = {publications/your-file.jpg}
#    4. Copy the TEMPLATE below, remove the leading "# ", fill it in, and paste
#       it under the matching year heading further down this file.
#    5. (Optional) Show it on a Research project page: in that project's body
#       add a cite tag for the citekey (see _projects/*.md — they already use
#       it). The paper then appears as a full card at the foot of that page.
#    6. Save / commit & push. Cloudflare rebuilds (~5 min) and the paper shows
#       on /publications/ (and on any project that cites it).
#
#  al-folio EXTRA fields (beyond standard BibTeX):
#    abstract     - paragraph shown on the paper's detail page
#    bibtex_show  - {true} adds a "Bib" dropdown button
#    doi          - DOI only, e.g. 10.3390/su17052250  (renders a DOI button)
#    html         - the publisher's full-text URL (renders an "HTML" button)
#    pdf          - a filename in /assets/pdf/ (or a full URL)
#    preview      - thumbnail; the value is relative to
#                   assets/img/publication_preview/  (so use publications/<file>)
#    selected     - {true} also lists it in the homepage "Selected" section
#    altmetric    - {true} shows an Altmetric badge (needs doi)
#    dimensions   - {true} shows a Dimensions citation badge (needs doi)
#  The PI's name (Golmohammadi, Golmar) is bolded automatically.
#
#  A ready-to-fill, copy-paste entry TEMPLATE lives in CMS-SETUP.md (section 5,
#  "Publications") — copy it from there. (The template can't be shown literally
#  here: a "@" inside this comment would be read as a real entry and break the
#  build.) A minimal entry needs: a citekey, title, author, journal, year, doi,
#  and html; add preview for a thumbnail.
# =============================================================================
---

